description: Vision Statement To share with the world, the various aspects of Hunza traditional Food in a manner that enhances both their holiday expectations and cultural curiosity. INTRODUCTION: Hidden Paradise Hunza formerly known as Ultar Restaurant is serving Healthy Hunza Traditional Food since the era for the first time tourism rushed to Valleys of Gilgit Baltistan. The concept behind a spot where only hunza food to serve is the mind of Mr. Lutfi Ali (Chef & Owner), also known as the founder of Hunza food. It was 1980’s when Mr. Lutfi Ali had a jeep and was affiliated with tours and expeditions and observed what tourism are attracting to or why the tourism are visiting the historical places, so why not they to attract towards Hunza Cultural Food as well, with a sudden decision he acquired a rented cabin and established a restaurant where he initiated to serve Apricot Soup and Apricot Juice. HISTORY Since 1980’s tourism attractions have improved and hotel business enhanced in the region and an outstanding market growth have witnessed from 1990’s to 2001.The concept of Traditional food business proved a remarkable results in comparison to other food businesses. Hidden paradise has been marketed by its own customers to be the best spot in hunza to eat and experience Traditional and Healthy Food. The restaurant by year 2000 has expanded its limited menu to list of 80 local food items.

description: The Lakhnavi celebrates a 200 year old culinary legacy tracing its lineage to the legendary chefs of the Nawabs of Awadh (Oudh) a.k.a the famous Qureshi family of Lucknow. As the culinary talent of the senior Qureshi chefs would have it the King was truly mesmerized by the food he had been served. He then invited the Qureshi's to cook in his royal kitchens. Each dish has been conceptualised & perfected by the duo for Avari Hotel; a pioneer in Lakhnavi cuisine, in Pakistan. The Lakhnavi is Pakistan’s first attempt at a traditional Sub-Continental fine dining restaurant.
